Github user hanm commented on the issue:

    https://github.com/apache/zookeeper/pull/126

    @eribeiro should we only change the document sources and generate the html/pdf in separate commit? There was a recent discussion on dev-list about this proposal and most folks leaning towards separation of doc source change and actual doc binary change. We can use ZOOKEEPER-2635 again before 3.5.3 release to regenerate everything.

Github user hanm commented on the issue:

    https://github.com/apache/zookeeper/pull/126

    @eribeiro I am thinking we can just change src/docs/src/documentation/skinconf.xml and leave other files in your original patch intact. What do you think?

Github user eribeiro commented on the issue:

    https://github.com/apache/zookeeper/pull/138

    @hanm I created a new PR for branch-3.4 (also applies to branch-3.5 and master) changing only the XML files as you have suggested on the previous PR.
